rComments: This class was a challenge, but well worth it.  Lyubansky is extremely intelligent and it shows.  He's awkwardly funny and well articulated, it's the other people in the class that made it unbearable; every time someone raised their hand, something stupid would come out.
he assigned an insane amount of readings, the tests were really hard and the TA was impossible. the material was interesting but i would recommend taking a different diversity class

do not take this class.  i think our psych dept has great teachers...this is not one of them.  he is vague, boring and not a good teacher.  his tests were crazy hard.  no one in our class seemed to like him...not even our TA.  do yourself a favor: even though the title sounds good, don't take this class...it is horrible
No Study guide, Prof gave lecture by reading from the slides and exam did not reflect any of the material from text book.  Do not recommend this Prof.
Pretty good teacher.  Provides a fairly balanced view.  The topic for my course was Race and Ethnicity.
He is less then helpful.  If the section is taught by someone else they have to better then him!

I took this class because I heard it was a very fun class.  Everyone I know got a C...The Professor graded the papers and tests rediculously hard!  I think he was trying to make the class hard for no reason..Do yourself a favor and wait until Dorothy Espelage teaches it the next semester.  She is supposed to be amazing!
